<TITLE> Dhaka to host international conference on disability </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 24 (bdnews24.com)-Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed will inaugurate a three-day international conference on disability, to be held at the Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre from Feb 27-29. The National Forum of Organisations Working with the Disabled (NFOWD) and the Asia Pacific Disability Forum (APDF) are organising the conference with the cooperation of the Bangladesh government, they said in a joint press conference Sunday. President of NFOWD Khandaker Zahurul Alam told bdnews24.com that the aim of the conference was to build a united and rights based society to support people with disabilities throughout the Asia Pacific region. This year's conference will work on implementing the principles that were adopted at the 2006 UN General Assembly to support people with disabilities. The theme of this year's conference is 'Disability and Development: Practical Strategies'. The chief adviser's special assistant for social welfare, MA Malek, and director of World Bank's Human Development Network, Nicholas Crafts, will be special guests. Director of UK-based Impact Foundation, Mansur Ahmed Chowdhury, will present the key-note paper in the conference. Forty-four papers from different countries will be presented at the conference. Some 450 representatives from 27 countries including 149 people with disabilities will participate in the conference. Participants from Bangladesh include chairperson of the National Disabled Development Foundation and former governor of Bangladesh Bank Dr Farash Uddin Ahmed, lawyer Dr Kamal Hossain, FBCCI administrator Syed Manzur Elahi, human rights worker Sultana Kamal, vice chancellor of BRAC University Jamilur Reza Chowdhury and Action Aid's Farah Kabir. bdnews2
